inBrief:
  text: "A free QuickBooks file review by a Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; diagnostic only, not the fix. We check reconciliation status, uncategorized and duplicate transactions, Undeposited Funds and Opening Balance Equity buildup, A/R-A/P aging integrity, payroll and sales-tax liability accounts, and file/version health. Plain-English findings, optional written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days, no obligation."
  source: "TechBrot &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team"
ctaBand:
  eyebrow: "Last call"
  heading: "Send the file. We&rsquo;ll tell you what it needs."
  lede: "Free diagnostic by a Certified ProAdvisor. Written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days if you want it fixed. No obligation."
  actions:
    - { label: "Get the free file review", href: "#file-review-form", class: "btn--primary" }
    - { label: "Speak to a ProAdvisor", href: "tel:+18777515575", class: "btn--ghost" }
aiSummary:
  - q: "What is a QuickBooks file review?"
    a: "<strong>A diagnostic, not a fix.</strong> A Certified ProAdvisor opens the actual file (Online or Desktop), runs a structured check across reconciliation, undeposited funds, A/R-A/P aging, liability accounts, and file health, and tells you in plain English what&rsquo;s working and what isn&rsquo;t. The review itself doesn&rsquo;t change a thing in your file &mdash; it&rsquo;s a read."
  - q: "What does the review cost?"
    a: "<strong>The review is free.</strong> If you want the file fixed, you get a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; no obligation, no pitch. Complex multi-entity or multi-year situations may need a paid deep diagnostic before an honest fixed-fee scope is possible, and we&rsquo;ll tell you that <em>before</em> anything costs money."
  - q: "How long does the review take?"
    a: "<strong>Typically 2&ndash;3 business days</strong> from the time we have accountant access to the file. Urgent cases (payroll deadlines, tax filings, file corruption) get prioritized &mdash; if you&rsquo;re on a deadline, say so on the form or call and we&rsquo;ll tell you whether we can hit it."
  - q: "What do you need from me?"
    a: "<strong>Accountant-user access to the QuickBooks file, plus the form on this page.</strong> For QuickBooks Online you add us as an accountant user from your own file (revocable any time, no password sharing). For QuickBooks Desktop an Accountant&rsquo;s Copy works, or a screenshare if the file is sensitive."
  - q: "Is my data safe?"
    a: "<strong>Yes.</strong> We work inside your own QuickBooks file via QuickBooks&rsquo; own accountant-access invitation &mdash; least-privilege access, no password sharing, revocable any time. Documents move through a secure share, not email attachments. We never extract or store your file outside QuickBooks for the review."
checks:
  - { title: "Reconciliation status, per account", body: "Every bank, credit-card, loan, and equity account either ties to source or it doesn&rsquo;t. We check the last reconciled date, the unreconciled balance, and whether the file is reconciling cleanly month-over-month or drifting." }
  - { title: "Uncategorized and duplicate transactions", body: "Buildup hiding behind a clean-looking P&amp;L. We pull the Uncategorized Income / Expense / Asset accounts, sweep the bank-rule duplicates, and quantify the noise so you know whether it&rsquo;s minutes of cleanup or weeks." }
  - { title: "Undeposited Funds and Opening Balance Equity buildup", body: "The two accounts that quietly carry years of error in most QuickBooks files. We read their balances, age the entries, and tell you whether you&rsquo;re looking at a workflow fix or a real cleanup." }
  - { title: "A/R-A/P aging integrity", body: "Is the aging report real, or is it polluted with stale invoices, applied-credits never cleared, and vendor bills paid outside the file? We sample the aged buckets and tell you what&rsquo;s actually collectible or owed." }
  - { title: "Payroll and sales-tax liability accounts", body: "The accounts most often wrong and most often missed at year-end &mdash; payroll liabilities, sales-tax payable, and the related reconciliation to the filed returns. We confirm whether the liability ledger ties out to the agency-filed numbers." }
  - { title: "File and version health", body: "File size and condense status, multi-user state, integration drift (Shopify, Stripe, banking, payroll), list integrity (chart of accounts, items, customers/vendors), and version/edition fit. The fundamentals that turn into expensive surprises when ignored." }
faq:
  - q: "What if the review uncovers more problems than I expected?"
    a: "That&rsquo;s exactly the point of the review &mdash; and it&rsquo;s still free. The Certified ProAdvisor tells you everything found, in plain English, ranked by what to fix first. The optional written fixed-fee scope is yours to decide on. Walk away with the findings and nothing else if you want; that happens regularly and we won&rsquo;t push back."
  - q: "Will I get pressured to buy ongoing monthly bookkeeping?"
    a: "No. The review is one engagement: read the file, tell you what it needs, optional written scope. If <a href=\"/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly\">monthly bookkeeping</a>, <a href=\"/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup\">cleanup</a>, or <a href=\"/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/?intent=catch-up\">catch-up</a> makes sense, we&rsquo;ll say so on the call &mdash; and if a one-time fix is the right answer, we&rsquo;ll say that too. We don&rsquo;t earn a commission for steering you anywhere."
  - q: "Can I just talk to a ProAdvisor on the phone first?"
    a: "Yes &mdash; call <a href=\"tel:+18777515575\" data-tb-event=\"phone_click\">(877) 751-5575</a> and a Certified ProAdvisor picks up during U.S. business hours. The form is faster for non-urgent reviews because we get the details before the call; the phone is faster for active emergencies (payroll deadlines, file corruption, unrecoverable errors)."
    phone: true
  - q: "We&rsquo;re a multi-entity or multi-year situation — does the free review still apply?"
    a: "The diagnostic-level read is still free for one entity. Multi-entity or multi-year files genuinely take longer to assess accurately, and may need a paid deep diagnostic before a fixed-fee scope is honest &mdash; typically a flat fee credited toward the engagement if you proceed. We&rsquo;ll tell you <em>before</em> the meter starts, on the discovery call, and you can stop there at no cost."
  - q: "Is the written fixed-fee scope binding?"
    a: "The scope binds us to the fee and the deliverables; it doesn&rsquo;t bind you. You can sit on it, take it to a different firm, or pass entirely. If you proceed, the fee in the scope is the fee we charge &mdash; no scope creep, no hourly upcharges, no &lsquo;we found more, here&rsquo;s a change order.&rsquo; If genuinely new in-scope work emerges mid-engagement, we re-quote in writing before any of it happens."
  - q: "Who actually reviews the file?"
    a: "A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor &mdash; typically our lead practice for the diagnostic itself. If the engagement after the review is best matched to a vetted local operator like Westgate Financial Services in Texas, we&rsquo;ll introduce you. The Certified ProAdvisor doing the review is the same person you talk to on the diagnostic call &mdash; never a rotating queue, never a junior offshore."
  - q: "What happens if you tell me the file is fine?"
    a: "Then it&rsquo;s fine, and you leave with that confirmation in writing. The reviewing ProAdvisor sends a brief note covering what was checked and what was confirmed clean. If an ongoing service would genuinely add value &mdash; <a href=\"/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly\">monthly bookkeeping</a>, year-end coordination &mdash; we&rsquo;ll mention it; if there isn&rsquo;t, we&rsquo;ll say nothing and you go on with your day. Call <a href=\"tel:+18777515575\" data-tb-event=\"phone_click\">(877) 751-5575</a> if you want to skip the form."
    phone: true
trustRow:
  - { value: "Free", label: "Diagnostic by a Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; not a sales call" }
  - { value: "4×", label: "QuickBooks ProAdvisor certifications &mdash; Online, Desktop, Enterprise &amp; Payroll" }
  - { value: "3 days", label: "Written fixed-fee scope after the review, if you want it fixed" }
  - { value: "1 day", label: "Response within one business day" }
---

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-bofu" id="file-review-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">The short version</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">What the free file review is &mdash; in one paragraph.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="file-review-tldr-body">Submit your QuickBooks file for a free Certified ProAdvisor review. We open the file, run a structured diagnostic across six areas &mdash; reconciliation, uncategorized and duplicate transactions, Undeposited Funds and Opening Balance Equity, A/R-A/P aging, payroll and sales-tax liability accounts, and file health &mdash; and tell you in plain English what we found and what it would take to fix. If you want it fixed, you get a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; from a <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">cleanup</a> to a <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/?intent=catch-up">catch-up</a> to ongoing <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping</a>, depending on what the file actually needs. No obligation. A review is diagnostic, not the fix &mdash; complex multi-entity or multi-year files may need a paid deep diagnostic, and we&rsquo;ll tell you that before anything costs money. The rest of <a href="/quickbooks/">our QuickBooks work</a> picks up after the diagnostic.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="file-review-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Five questions, answered plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="file-review-checks">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What we check</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six places a QuickBooks file goes wrong.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The structured diagnostic the reviewing ProAdvisor runs against your file. None of it touches your books &mdash; it&rsquo;s a read, not a change.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for item in checks %}
      <li><strong>{{ item.title | safe }}</strong>{{ item.body | safe }}</li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="file-review-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How the review works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From form submission to plain-English findings.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">01</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Submit</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Short form. No credit card. Tell us the QuickBooks version and what you&rsquo;re seeing.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">02</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">ProAdvisor review</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">A Certified ProAdvisor opens the file (via accountant access) and runs the structured diagnostic &mdash; typically within 2&ndash;3 business days.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">03</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Plain-English findings</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">A short call, then a written summary. What&rsquo;s working, what isn&rsquo;t, what&rsquo;s at risk, and what it would take to fix.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">04</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Optional written scope</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Fixed-fee, in writing, within 3 business days of the diagnostic call &mdash; if you want it fixed. No obligation, no pitch.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

